item.title: Jens Voigt Crash Stage 16 Tour de France 2009
item.description:
Jens Voigt Crash Stage 16 Tour de France 2009
Full Analysis Of Crash Here : http://cozybeehive.blogspot.com/2009/07/was-it-jens-voigts-steerer-tube.html I literally winced in pain when I saw Jens go down today. He crashed right on his face on the second descent down La Rosiere in today's stage. The hairpin bends are really trecherous down this road. He must have been going over 60kph when he apparently hit something nasty on the road. Here's hoping nothing serious happened to him. As Phil Liggett said today, the developers long ago may have found that they were running out of land to build roads so they built this descent to get down to the bottom of the mountain as quickly as possible. Sorry for poor video quality, but I took it real quick.
